casebody.data:
No. 119,

Misc.

Jordan v. United States. Charles A. Horsky for petitioner. Solicitor General Rankin, Assistant Attorney General Olney, Beatrice Rosenberg and Felicia Dubrovsky for the United States. Per Curiam:

The motion for leave to proceed in forma pauperis and the petition for writ of certiorari are granted. The judgment of the Court of Appeals is vacated and the cause is remanded to the District Court for consideration on the merits.
